<org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-W5jU55-Q8I3lKPqd-_8N7Q" name="trainer,_abH0YFMLEd-b9rMLu3PL1w" guid="-W5jU55-Q8I3lKPqd-_8N7Q" changeDate="2010-10-28T13:40:05.850-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>This role is responsible for delivering training to users in order to prepare them to use the product (result of the&#xD;
project) and become proficient in using the product, in such a way that the project team can transfer the ownership of the&#xD;
product to the customer.</mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Training may be first delivered to a test audience so the trainer can collect feedback and make adjustments to the&#xD;
    training material before rolling out the training to&amp;nbsp;other users.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For scalability purposes, training may be delivered to other trainers first, who will then educate a large population&#xD;
    of end users.&#xD;
&lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
  <skills>A person performing this role needs to have excellent verbal and non-verbal communication skills, and the ability to teach&#xD;
concepts and ideas, and&amp;nbsp;illustrate them with real-life examples preferably based on his or her own experience.</skills>
  <assignmentApproaches>Some companies have in-house trainers, some prefer to hire training companies to deliver the training needed by a project&#xD;
or enterprise.</assignmentApproaches>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
